sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Pipeline
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS
    participant Worker1 as Worker Pod 1
    participant Worker2 as Worker Pod 2
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>openshift-monitoring

    Note over User,Prom: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>443->9443/TCP, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response (admit/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created / Rejected

    Note over Operator,Kubelet: Reconciliation Loop

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: PyTorchJob created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods, Services, NetworkPolicy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Kubelet: Schedule Pods<br/>10250/TCP HTTPS
    Kubelet-->>K8sAPI: Pod Running
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Worker1,Worker2: Flow 2: Distributed Training Execution

    Worker1->>Worker1: DNS lookup via Headless Service
    Worker1->>Worker2: Training data exchange<br/>framework-specific port/TCP<br/>plaintext (intra-cluster)
    Worker2->>Worker1: Gradient sync<br/>framework-specific port/TCP<br/>plaintext (intra-cluster)

    Note over Prom,Operator: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prom->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None (PodMonitor)
    Operator-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics
